# Code Style Rules for annashmitko.com

## General
- Project uses TypeScript with Astro framework
- Tab indentation: 2 spaces
- Line endings: LF (Unix-style)
- Maximum line length: ~80-100 characters
- UTF-8 encoding

## TypeScript/JavaScript
- Use ES modules (import/export)
- Use single quotes for string literals
- Include semicolons at the end of statements
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for component names and interfaces
- Strongly type interfaces and component props

## Astro Components
- Script section at the top with --- delimiters
- Define interfaces with Props prefix for component props
- Destructure props from Astro.props
- Component markup follows script section

## HTML/JSX
- Use double quotes for HTML attributes
- Close self-closing tags with a forward slash
- Use className instead of class for dynamic classes
- Interpolate variables with curly braces: {variable}

## CSS/Styling
- Primary styling through Tailwind classes
- Component-specific styles in <style> blocks
- Use kebab-case for CSS classes
- Group related Tailwind classes together
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Naming Conventions
- Files: PascalCase for components (Card.astro)
- Directories: lowercase with semantic naming (pages, components, layouts)
- Component props: camelCase
- CSS classes: kebab-case

## Project Structure
- /src/pages: Route pages
- /src/components: Reusable UI components
- /src/layouts: Page layout templates
- /src/content: Markdown content

## Best Practices
- Use appropriate accessibility attributes
- Include rel="noopener noreferrer" with target="_blank" links
- Organize imports with framework imports first, followed by local imports
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add meaningful comments for complex logic